        "created_at": "2025-07-21T00:30:37.386Z",
        "cooked": "<h3><a name=\"p-272314-feature-request-1\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-272314-feature-request-1\" aria-label=\"Heading link\"></a>Feature Request</h3>\n<p>Please add a setting to <strong>always show the “Send” button</strong> (the paper plane icon) in the message input area, even when the input field is empty.</p>\n<h3><a name=\"p-272314-motivation-2\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-272314-motivation-2\" aria-label=\"Heading link\"></a>Motivation</h3>\n<p>Some users prefer to use the mouse instead of the keyboard, or may find it more intuitive to always have a visible “Send” button regardless of whether text is currently entered. This can improve usability, especially for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>elderly users,</li>\n<li>people switching from other messengers,</li>\n<li>accessibility purposes.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><a name=\"p-272314-suggested-implementation-3\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-272314-suggested-implementation-3\" aria-label=\"Heading link\"></a>Suggested implementation</h3>\n<p>Add a toggle in the settings such as:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"chcklst-box checked fa fa-square-check-o\"></span> Always show “Send” button</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This would display the button in a disabled (greyed-out) state when there’s no input, and make it active once text is entered — similar to how other messaging apps behave.</p>\n<p>Thank you for considering this request!</p>",
